cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.LG. 

The paper explores peer-interaction effects in online networks on speaking skill development, which suggests a focus on social networks and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The use of Graph Signal Processing (GSP) also suggests a potential fit with cs.SD (Sound), while the focus on prediction models and regression suggests a potential fit with cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
